      		    <div class="panel equal">
      		    <h3>Features</h3>
          		<p>
          		  The template features a sliding, off-canvas sidebar, with a column of icons when the menu is in 'small'mode. I've already included the Foundation Icons set, as these are used by the sidebar.
          		</p>
          		<p>
      		      If you have a suggestion for improvement, please submit a pull request on Github or contact me.
      		    </p>
      		    </div>
          	</div>
          	<div class="large-4 medium-4 columns" data-equalizer-watch>
              <div class="panel equal">
              <h3>Customise</h3>
          		<p>
          		  There's only 250 lines of CSS complementing Foundation, so it should be easy to find your way around.
          		  The ALXS Sidebar navigation template is ideal for beginner web designers/developer who are looking for a nice template to get them started, or for someon just learning about mobile-first and responsive web design.
          		</p>
